text.section:
In accordance with the record retention and disposal schedules, a public official shall offer to the Archives any public record of the official that no longer is needed, such as:
an original paper;
a book;
a file;
a record of a court of record for which an accurate transcript is in use; or
a record that relates to the internal management of or otherwise is a housekeeping record for an office of a clerk of court or register of wills.
